n the numbers of explicitly integrable splitting sub-Hamiltonians are as\nsmall as possible, such splitting Hamiltonian methods would bring better\naccuracies. In this case, the optimized fourth-order partitioned Runge-Kutta\nand Runge-Kutta-Nystr\\\"{o}m methods are worth recommending.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 9 Jan 2022 04:22:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-30"}
